Photo: Screenshot Via Instagram Image 45 of 45 Johnny Manziel and girlfriend pulled over after domestic dispute on road, alcohol involved 1 / 45 Back to Gallery Johnny Manziel was pulled over by Avon, Ohio police earlier this week after police said a domestic argument between the beleaguered Browns quarterback and his girlfriend got out of hand on Interstate 90, according to a report by Cleveland's ABC WEWS NewsChannel5 .
According to the police report obtained by the station — which has not been released yet — both Manziel and his girlfriend were drinking, though neither were charged.
A witness told police she saw the couple arguing as they passed her on the shoulder at high speeds, and Manziel's girlfriend, Colleen Crowley, attempted to exit the vehicle while they were still moving.
Crowley reportedly told police Manziel pushed her head into a window, though an abrasion on Crowley's arm was determined by police to come from an attempt by Manziel to keep her from leaving the vehicle.
Crowley told officers she did not want to press chargers.
If the reports are true, this is yet another disturbing chapter in the ongoing Johnny Manziel saga.
Earlier this year, Manziel checked into rehab for treatment of alcohol addiction following a string of incidents and erratic behavior.
Shortly after the report of the feud surfaced Crowley released a statement on her Instagram account claiming "it was just an argument" and that she and Manziel are "all good."
UPDATE: Browns' general manager Ray Farmer released an official statement regarding the Manziel incident, per ESPN's Adam Schefter :
"We were aware of the situation. It is a matter that we take seriously and have expressed our concerns to Johnny directly. Those conversations will remain private and we will refrain from further comment at this time."
